org.waarp.openr66.client

Class MultipleSubmitTransfer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.waarp.openr66.client.AbstractTransfer
      • org.waarp.openr66.client.SubmitTransfer
        • org.waarp.openr66.client.MultipleSubmitTransfer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable

    public class MultipleSubmitTransfer
extends SubmitTransfer
    Client to submit a transfer for multiple files to multiple hosts at once.
    Files will have to be separated by ','.
    Hosts will have to be separated by ','.

    For instance: -to host1,host2,host3 -file file1,file2
    Will generate:
    -to host1 -file file1
    -to host1 -file file2
    -to host2 -file file1
    -to host2 -file file2
    -to host3 -file file1
    -to host3 -file file2


    Extra option is -client which allows the filename resolution on remote (recv files) when using wildcards.
